Simple game server.


The eumi package can be run from the command line like this:

  python -m eumi

Or, you can use the run.py script:

  python run.py

But it must either be in the same directory as the eumi package or that
package must be installed in your system or Python virtual environment.


A brief outline of the source code.

├── LICENSE - GNU GPL v3
├── README  - This file.
│
├── eumi - Self-editable web server.
│    │
│    ├── __init__.py  - Make this dir into a Python package.
│    ├── __main__.py  - Allows 'python -m eumi' to start server.
│    ├── argparser.py - Parse command line arguments.
│    │
│    ├── html.py - Simple and flexible HTML generator.
│    ├── main.py - WSGI app, and functions to run it.
│    ├── page.py - Page rendering.
│    ├── page_actions.py - Code for page actions.
│    ├── server.py - Server.
│    │
│    └── joy - Powerful language by Manfred von Thun,
│             see links below for more information.
│
├── run.py - Script to run the server.
│
└── server.pyckle - The saved content, default file.



Links to more information on Joy:

  http://www.latrobe.edu.au/humanities/research/research-projects/past-projects/joy-programming-language
  http://www.kevinalbrecht.com/code/joy-mirror/index.html
  http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joy_%28programming_language%29
